FAQ’s

Common Doubts

Find answers to common queries about SkyTrack's features, usage, and integration possibilities.

1. What is SkyTrack in simple words?

SkyTrack is an advanced 3D tracking system designed for real-time monitoring of individuals, vehicles, and assets. It provides precise location data, including height and depth, for emergency, family, vehicle, and legal tracing.

2. When is SkyTrack launching?

SkyTrack will officially launch on January 1, 2026.

3. How does 3D tracking work?

SkyTrack uses advanced technology to track not only horizontal positions but also vertical (altitude) data, allowing for comprehensive location tracking in 3D space.

4. Can I integraten to 3rd-party apps?

Yes, SkyTrack offers seamless in-app integration with third-party apps, making it easy to share data and track across multiple platforms.

5. Is SkyTrack secure to use?

SkyTrack prioritizes privacy and security, using state-of-the-art encryption and authentication protocols to protect your data.

6. Can I track multiple people at once?

Yes, SkyTrack allows you to track multiple devices or people simultaneously, providing real-time updates across all monitored assets.

7. How do I join the waitlist?

Simply visit our waitlist page and sign up with your email to get priority access and exclusive updates.

8. What devices are compatible?

SkyTrack is designed to work with a variety of mobile devices and smart platforms, ensuring wide compatibility for users across different ecosystems.

9. Will it be available internationally?

Yes, SkyTrack will be available for use worldwide, with support for multiple regions and languages.

10. What are the benefits of waitlist?

As an early adopter, you'll get exclusive access to SkyTrack's advanced features, priority support, and special perks only available to our first users.
